'''Kevin Randolph Coble''' is a member of the [[Northwestern Wildcats men's basketball|Northwestern Wildcats basketball team]]. He led the Wildcats in [[point (basketball)|scoring]] and [[rebound (basketball)|rebounding]] as a freshman, sophomore and junior during the 2006-07, 2007-08 and 2008-09 seasons,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/teams/stats?teamId=77&year=2007|title=Northwestern Wildcats Statistics - 2006-07|accessdate=2010-03-09|publisher=[[ESPN.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/teams/stats?teamId=77&year=2008|title=Northwestern Wildcats Statistics - 2007-08|accessdate=2010-03-09|publisher=[[ESPN.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/teams/stats?teamId=77&year=2009|title=Northwestern Wildcats Statistics - 2008-09|accessdate=2010-03-09|publisher=[[ESPN.com]]}}</ref> but was injured and [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirt]]ted during his true senior season.  Following the [[2008<U+2013>09 Big Ten Conference men's basketball season|2008<U+2013>09 All-Big Ten Conference regular season]], he was named a second-team All-conference selection by both the coaches and the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bigten.cstv.com/auto_pdf/p_hotos/s_chools/big10/sports/m-baskbl/auto_pdf/2009AllBigTen|title=2008<U+2013>09 All-Big Ten Men<U+2019>s Basketball Team|accessdate=2009-03-12|date=2008-03-09|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref> He was also named Big Ten men's basketball player of the week during the season.<ref name=CCEBTWH>{{cite web|url=http://bigten.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/012609aac.html|title=Coble, Cornley Earn Big Ten's Weekly Honors: Northwestern's Kevin Coble and Penn State's Jamelle Cornley lauded for performances through the week ending January 25. |accessdate=2009-03-09|date=2009-01-26|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref>  He was an honorable mention All-Big Ten selection following the [[2007<U+2013>08 Big Ten Conference men's basketball season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bigten.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/031008aag.html|title=Indiana's White Named Big Ten Player of the Year by Coaches and Media: Purdue's Painter claims Coach of the Year accolades, Boilermakers' Kramer nabs Defensive Player of the Year honors, Hoosier Gordon earns Freshman of the Year laurels, and Wisconsin's Bohannon collects Sixth Man of the Year honor|accessdate=2009-03-06|date=2008-03-10|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref>

